        "text": "*[Bug 19008] on.exit() at top level is a silent no-op*\n<https:\/\/bugs.r-project.org\/show_bug.cgi?id=19008>\n\nLuke Tierney (<mailto:luke@stat.uiowa.edu|luke@stat.uiowa.edu>) changed:\n\n           What    |Removed                     |Added\n----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n                 CC|                            |luke@stat.uiowa.edu\n             Status|UNCONFIRMED                 |CONFIRMED\n     Ever confirmed|0                           |1\n\n--- Comment #1 from Luke Tierney (<mailto:luke@stat.uiowa.edu|luke@stat.uiowa.edu>) ---\n(In reply to Kevin Ushey from comment #0)\n&gt; For example, consider the script:\n&gt; \n&gt; ```\n&gt; on.exit(print(\"exit\"))\n&gt; ```\n&gt; \n&gt; This exit handler will not be executed if at the top-level; e.g. if executed\n&gt; via something like `R -f script.R`. However, it will be executed if run via\n&gt; `source(\"script.R\")`.\n&gt; \n&gt; Is this intentional? If so, I think it's worth documenting this caveat more\n&gt; explicitly in `?on.exit`. Strictly speaking, I believe it behaves as\n&gt; documented, since in the `Rscript -f script.R` example there indeed is no\n&gt; parent function context for `on.exit()` to attach to, but that is likely\n&gt; only apparent to R experts.\n\nIt is consistent with the documentation. I can't see how the `Rscript` case\nwould be surprising. The `source()` case may be, but many things can be\nsurprising when `eval()` is involved. I don't think there would be any harm in\nsignaling a warning, or maybe even an error, when no current function is found,\nbut I'm not sure it is worth it.\n\n&gt; If not, it would be helpful if these handlers could be registered and\n&gt; executed on process exit at some appropriate point.\n\nI don't think overloading `on.exit` for this would be a good idea. A separate\nmechanism could be added for this but it would be a fair bit of work and I'm\nnot sure it is worth the effort. `reg.finalizer` is already available for some\nof this. If you want to pursue this you can submit a WISHLIST item, preferably\nwith a proposed patch.\n\nI'll leave this open for now, but my current inclination is to close as\nWONTFIX.\n\n&gt; For posterity, I bumped into this with code of the form:\n&gt; \n&gt; ```\n&gt; conn &lt;- socketConnection(...)\n&gt; on.exit(close(conn))\n&gt; ```\n&gt; \n&gt; ---\n&gt; \n&gt; ```\n&gt; &gt; utils::sessionInfo()\n&gt; R version 4.5.1 (2025-06-13)\n&gt; Platform: aarch64-apple-darwin20\n&gt; Running under: macOS Tahoe 26.2\n&gt; ```",
