        "text": "*[Bug 18972] diff(x=&lt;m-by-n&gt;, l, d) drops dimensions when l*d &gt;= m*\n<https:\/\/bugs.r-project.org\/show_bug.cgi?id=18972>\n\n--- Comment #10 from Suharto Anggono (<mailto:suharto_anggono@yahoo.com|suharto_anggono@yahoo.com>) ---\n(In reply to Suharto Anggono from comment #5)\n&gt; Created attachment 3572\n&gt; No early return for lag * differences &gt;= xlen\n\nInstead of\n\n    r[if (lag &lt; (len &lt;- nrow(r))) -len:-(len - lag + 1) else integer(), , drop\n= FALSE]\n\nand\n\n    r[if (lag &lt; (len &lt;- length(r))) -len:-(len - lag + 1L) else integer()]\n\n, now I prefer\n\n    r[-nrow(r):-max(nrow(r) - lag + 1L, 1L), , drop = FALSE]\n\nand\n\n    r[-length(r):-max(length(r) - lag + 1L, 1L)]\n\n.",
        "username": "r-bugs notifier",
        "icons": {
            "emoji": ":robot_face:"
        },
